    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "Isaiah",
        "delineation": "Chapter",
        "number": 57,
        "summary": "When the righteous die, they enter into peace\u2014Mercy is promised to the penitent\u2014There is no peace for the wicked.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "The righteous perisheth, and no man layeth it to heart: and merciful men are taken away, none considering that the righteous is taken away from the evil to come.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 59:2 (1\u20132).",
                        "start": 14,
                        "end": 23
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 43,
                        "end": 45
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 73,
                        "end": 76
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 153,
                        "end": 161
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "He shall enter into peace: they shall rest in their beds, each one walking in his uprightness.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Paradise.",
                        "start": 20,
                        "end": 25
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 58,
                        "end": 66
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 75,
                        "end": 77
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "But draw near hither, ye sons of the sorceress, the seed of the adulterer and the whore.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "IE\u00a0people affiliated with evil; see vv.\u00a04\u20135.",
                        "start": 25,
                        "end": 29
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Sexual Immorality.",
                        "start": 64,
                        "end": 73
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Against whom do ye sport yourselves? against whom make ye a wide mouth, and draw out the tongue? are ye not children of transgression, a seed of falsehood,",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 1:4.",
                        "start": 108,
                        "end": 116
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 72,
                        "end": 75
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 97,
                        "end": 100
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Enflaming yourselves with idols under every green tree, slaying the children in the valleys under the clifts of the rocks?",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Kgs. 14:23 (22\u201323); 2\u00a0Kgs. 16:4 (2\u20134).",
                        "start": 26,
                        "end": 31
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "IE\u00a0participating in abominable cult sacrifices. Jer. 7:31; 32:35.",
                        "start": 56,
                        "end": 63
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ezek. 16:20.",
                        "start": 68,
                        "end": 76
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Among the smooth stones of the stream is thy portion; they, they are thy lot: even to them hast thou poured a drink offering, thou hast offered a meat offering. Should I receive comfort in these?",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "type": "paper-page-number",
                        "data": 930
                    }
                ],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 17,
                        "end": 23
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 38,
                        "end": 40
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 65,
                        "end": 68
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Upon a lofty and high mountain hast thou set thy bed: even thither wentest thou up to offer sacrifice.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "IE\u00a0as an altar for idolatrous use.",
                        "start": 49,
                        "end": 52
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Behind the doors also and the posts hast thou set up thy remembrance: for thou hast discovered thyself to another than me, and art gone up; thou hast enlarged thy bed, and made thee a covenant with them; thou lovedst their bed where thou sawest it.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "HEB\u00a0exposed.",
                        "start": 84,
                        "end": 94
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 95,
                        "end": 113
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 182,
                        "end": 192
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 245,
                        "end": 248
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And thou wentest to the king with ointment, and didst increase thy perfumes, and didst send thy messengers far off, and didst debase thyself even unto hell.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "HEB\u00a0melech or molech (a horrible idol).",
                        "start": 24,
                        "end": 28
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 133,
                        "end": 145
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Thou art wearied in the greatness of thy way; yet saidst thou not, There is no hope: thou hast found the life of thine hand; therefore thou wast not grieved.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Jer. 18:12 (11\u201312).",
                        "start": 79,
                        "end": 83
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "IE\u00a0renewal of strength.",
                        "start": 105,
                        "end": 123
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 46,
                        "end": 49
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And of whom hast thou been afraid or feared, that thou hast lied, and hast not remembered me, nor laid it to thy heart? have not I held my peace even of old, and thou fearest me not?",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 3:7.",
                        "start": 37,
                        "end": 43
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 78:36 (35\u201337).",
                        "start": 60,
                        "end": 64
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 103,
                        "end": 105
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "I will declare thy righteousness, and thy works; for they shall not profit thee.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 1:3.",
                        "start": 7,
                        "end": 14
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "When thou criest, let thy companies deliver thee; but the wind shall carry them all away; vanity shall take them: but he that putteth his trust in me shall possess the land, and shall inherit my holy mountain;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Lands of Inheritance.",
                        "start": 200,
                        "end": 208
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 108,
                        "end": 113
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And shall say, Cast ye up, cast ye up, prepare the way, take up the stumblingblock out of the way of my people.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "HEB\u00a0And he shall say.",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 13
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 62:10.",
                        "start": 39,
                        "end": 46
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Jacob 4:14 (13\u201314).",
                        "start": 68,
                        "end": 82
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For thus saith the high and lofty One that inhabiteth eternity, whose name is Holy; I dwell in the high and holy place, with him also that is of a contrite and humble spirit, to revive the spirit of the humble, and to revive the heart of the contrite ones.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0God, Eternal Nature of.",
                        "start": 54,
                        "end": 62
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Luke 1:49.",
                        "start": 78,
                        "end": 82
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Contrite Heart.",
                        "start": 147,
                        "end": 155
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Humility.",
                        "start": 160,
                        "end": 166
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 61:1.",
                        "start": 178,
                        "end": 184
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Poor in Spirit.",
                        "start": 203,
                        "end": 209
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 75,
                        "end": 77
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 113,
                        "end": 119
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 134,
                        "end": 141
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "For I will not contend for ever, neither will I be always wroth: for the spirit should fail before me, and the souls which I have made.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Micah 7:18; D&C 1:33.",
                        "start": 15,
                        "end": 22
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Moses 3:7.",
                        "start": 111,
                        "end": 116
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 117,
                        "end": 122
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "For the iniquity of his covetousness was I wroth, and smote him: I hid me, and was wroth, and he went on frowardly in the way of his heart.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 63:32.",
                        "start": 8,
                        "end": 16
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ezek. 33:31.",
                        "start": 24,
                        "end": 36
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "HEB\u00a0turning away.",
                        "start": 105,
                        "end": 114
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "I have seen his ways, and will heal him: I will lead him also, and restore comforts unto him and to his mourners.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 112:10.",
                        "start": 48,
                        "end": 52
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Comfort.",
                        "start": 75,
                        "end": 83
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Sorrow.",
                        "start": 104,
                        "end": 112
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "I create the fruit of the lips; Peace, peace to him that is far off, and to him that is near, saith the Lord; and I will heal him.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "IE\u00a0speech. Heb. 13:15.",
                        "start": 13,
                        "end": 18
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Acts 2:39.",
                        "start": 60,
                        "end": 63
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 48,
                        "end": 59
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 76,
                        "end": 87
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "But the wicked are like the troubled sea, when it cannot rest, whose waters cast up mire and dirt.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Wickedness.",
                        "start": 8,
                        "end": 14
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 15,
                        "end": 18
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "There is no peace, saith my God, to the wicked.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Conscience; Peace.",
                        "start": 12,
                        "end": 17
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 8
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
    }
}